**DPSYC 607 — Research Methods and Statistical Analysis**  
Advanced graduate course covering quantitative and qualitative research design, statistical analysis, and interpretation of results in educational and psychological research.

**DPSYC 602 — Literacy and Language Development**  
Examination of theoretical perspectives and empirical research on literacy acquisition and language development in childhood and adolescence.

**DPSYC 505 — Personality: Theoretical Approaches and Evolutionary Course**  
Survey of major personality theories from psychodynamic and trait perspectives to evolutionary and biological approaches.

**DPSYC 503 — Learning: Theoretical Approaches and Educational Applications**  
Review of classical and contemporary theories of learning and their practical applications in educational settings.
